modules.description: Parses Markdown files into an abstract syntax tree, supporting elements like headers, lists, and links. It processes strings and file inputs, producing structured data for further manipulation. Used to convert user-generated content into HTML or other formatted outputs.

This module handles text parsing and transformation tasks, focusing on structured markdown processing through operations like text normalization, delimiter scanning, and state management. It works with strings, custom types such as `paragraph`, `text`, and `ref`, along with parse states and buffers to manage complex formatting rules. Use cases include converting markdown content into organized data structures or processing text with nested elements like lists, links, and escaped characters.

Converts Markdown elements to HTML, handling text, paragraphs, and inline content with custom rendering for links and images. Processes structured document fragments, including headings, lists, and blockquotes, using type-safe callbacks. Generates phrasing or block-level HTML elements based on input Markdown constructs.
